# Nginx + Docker Compose Project

## Objective

Deploy a static website using Nginx and Docker Compose.

## Project Structure

```text
nginx-compose/
├── docker-compose.yml
└── index.html
```

## Docker Compose File

* Used the official Nginx image.
* Exposed port 8081 on the host.
* Mounted the local HTML file into the container using a bind mount.

## Concepts Learned

### Port Mapping

```yaml
ports:
  - "8081:80"
```

Host port 8081 forwards traffic to port 80 inside the Nginx container.

### Bind Mount

```yaml
volumes:
  - ./index.html:/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
```

The local HTML file is directly mounted into the container.

### Nginx

Nginx serves static web content and is commonly used as a web server and reverse proxy.

